 central Seto Inland Sea (2009) Aquaculture Science, 57, pp. 233-241; Nagasawa, T., Yamashita, Y., Yamada, H., Early life history of mebaru, Sebastes inermis (Scorpaenidae), in Sendai Bay, Japan (2000) Japanese Journal of Ichthyology, 47, pp. 231-241; Plaza, G., Katayama, S., Omori, M., Daily patterns of settlement and individual growth rates of young-of-the-year of the rock-fish Sebastes inermis in a Sargassum bed (2010) Fisheries Research, 103, pp. 48-55; Rose, G.A., On distributional responses of North Atlantic fish to climate change (2005) ICES Journal of Marine Science, 62 (7), pp. 1360-1374. , DOI 10.1016/j.icesjms.2005.05.007, PII S1054313905001013, Influence of Climate Change on North Atlantic Fish Stocks; Senta, T., Kinoshita, I., Larval and juvenile fishes occurring in surf zones of western Japan (1985) Transactions of the American Fisheries Society, 114, pp. 609-618; Takasuka, A., Oozeki, Y., Aoki, I., Optimal growth temperature hypothesis: Why do anchovy flourish and sardine collapse or vice versa under the same ocean regime? (2007) Canadian Journal of Fisheries and Aquatic Sciences, 64 (5), pp. 768-776. , DOI 10.1139/F07-052","Shoji, J.; Takehara Fisheries Research Laboratory, 5-8-1 Minato-machi, Takehara, Hiroshima 725-0024, Japan; email: jshoji@hiroshima-u.ac.jp",,,,,,,,10543139,,ICESE,,"English","ICES J. Mar. Sci.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-79959529865
